summary:
Manila Labor Day Vibe
So in the span of this afternoon, I had attend a wedding event along with my college friends. Event was...
body:
Manila Labor Day Vibe

So in the span of this afternoon, I had attend a wedding event along with my college friends. Event was really a challenging for me since they hired me as the shooter for their special day. One thing that really frustrates me is that I feel like my skills had just go back on being amateur as I scroll through on my shots and the guests who keeps on taking photos in front of me with their tab and phones as if they’re the main shooter of the event.

Looks like I’m gonna be doing a lot of editings on the photo this upcoming week.

blog.title: fragments of broken dreams . . .
blog.description:
All the photographs posted here are original work from photographers I follow  on tumblr . My aim is  twofold, share the inspiration, and give photographers a bit more exposure .     
 I am also part of the  Lux Lit  team of rebloggers, and ms-excuse me with Thierry Facon, where the main focus is to bring you lesser known photographs that we feel deserve some more attention. 
 Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions or comments, or would  like me to check out your blog;  I'm on a constant quest for new photography blogs to follow .
julesfalkhunter@gmail.com
